description: Insomniac Games attackers have released over 1.3 million documents that reveal Sony and Marvel contracts, game details, and personal data.

title: Here’s what happened in crypto today
description:
Need to know what happened in crypto today? Here is the latest news on daily trends and events impacting Bitcoin price, blockchain, DeFi, NFTs, Web3 and crypto regulation.

FTX debtors and liquidators have reached a proposed settlement on how to distribute funds to users of the failed crypto exchange. Meanwhile, Montenegro's appeals court has thrown out a November decision by the country’s high court that the legal conditions for the former Terra CEO’s extradition had been met, and a U.S. federal court has approved the settlement between Binance and the Commodities Future and Trading Commission (CFTC).

Debtors for FTX have reached a settlement with the failed crypto firm's liquidators — though the agreement is subject to approval by the United States Bankruptcy Court for the District of Delaware and the Supreme Court of the Bahamas. 

According to the proposed settlement, all FTX users who don't have claims pending with the court will be paid in United States dollars for losses in cash or digital assets. Nonfungible tokens are exempt from these terms. Eligible claimants can vote on the reimbursement plan in the second quarter of next year.

title: Court prevents DCG from altering Genesis ownership
